transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra, Quinn speaking, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I really just wanted to try your product.

Speaker 1: Somehow I'm on a subscription basis or something.

Speaker 2: I didn't order this for you.

Speaker 1: Second, you can order this when you want, sir.

Speaker 2: I can take a look for you.

Speaker 1: You do not have to get this automatically.

Speaker 2: We can see what's going on and why that's like that for you and fix it.

Speaker 1: One moment, let me just pull up your account.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I didn't realize that.

Speaker 1: My wife just had surgery, so I haven't even tried.

Speaker 2: I had to try the first round prescription, and last week I got a second one.

Speaker 1: Okay, I understand.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so basically you can set this up for the day and month that you want to get it,

Speaker 1: or you can basically do this as needed if that works for you better in a five-month time frame.

Speaker 2: Well, I think you just cancel it for now.

Speaker 1: Okay, yeah, we'll be canceling your prescription.

Speaker 2: We can definitely do that for you, but just to say to you, we can just kind of leave it open,

Speaker 1: and you can call in for your next refills in the next five months as well.

Speaker 2: What happens after five months?

Speaker 1: Whatever you would like to happen.

Speaker 2: It would be up to you.

Speaker 1: You can request more time.

Speaker 2: You can get an order.

Speaker 1: It's up to you.

Speaker 2: Well, I don't want to be charged again.

Speaker 1: Let's just cancel it, and I'll call if I want it.

Speaker 2: Yeah, but you won't have a prescription if you cancel it.

Speaker 1: What do you mean, sir?

Speaker 2: Like you can't get anything from the pharmacy without a prescription?

Speaker 1: Okay, it's fine.

Speaker 2: Just cancel it.

Speaker 1: Okay, well, I'll do that for you.

Speaker 2: Anything else you need?

Speaker 1: No, you got my information?

Speaker 2: Yes, Eric Kruger.

Speaker 1: Yeah, can you send me a confirmation that I'm canceled?

Speaker 2: We don't have an e-mail confirmation,

Speaker 1: just a verbal confirmation that your prescription is terminated.

Speaker 2: You will not receive this again, sir.

Speaker 1: Okay, great.

Speaker 2: Thank you.
